  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  sourcePage 4
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line 4
  line `( c ) amounts received from the appropriate Government, or any amount received from any other source`
  line `whose r epayment is guaranteed by the appropriate Government, or any amount received from a statutory`
  line `authority constituted under an Act of Parliament or a State Legislature;`
  line `( d ) amounts received from foreign Governments, foreign or international banks, multilater al`
  line `financial institutions, foreign Government owned development financial institutions, foreign export`
  line `credit collaborators, foreign bodies corporate, foreign citizens, foreign authorities or person resident`
  line `outside India subject to the provisions of the F oreign Exchange Management Act, 1999 (42 of 1999)`
  line `and the rules and regulations made thereunder;`
  line `( e ) amounts received by way of contributions towards the capital by partners of any partnership`
  line `firm or a limited liability partnership;`
  line `( f ) amounts received by an individual by way of loan from his relatives or amounts received by any`
  line `firm by way of loan from the relatives of any of its partners;`
  line `( g ) amounts received as credit by a buyer from a seller on the sale of any property (whether`
  line `movable or immovable);`
  line `( h ) amounts received by an asset re - construction company which is registered with the Reserve`
  line `Bank of India under section 3 of the Securitisation and Reconstruction of Financial Assets and`
  line `Enforcement of Security Interest Act, 2002 (54 of 2002);`
  line `( i ) any deposit made under section 34 or an amount accepted by a political party under section 29B`
  line `of the Representation of the People Act, 1951 (43 of 1951);`
  line `( j ) any periodic payment made by the members of the self - help groups operating within such`
  line `ceilings as m ay be prescribed by the State Government or Union territory Government;`
  line `( k ) any other amount collected for such purpose and within such ceilings as may be prescribed by`
  line `the State Government;`
  line `( l ) an amount received in the course of, or for the purpose of, business and bearing a genuine`
  line `connection to such business including —`
  line `( i ) payment, advance or part payment for the supply or hire of goods or provision of services and`
  line `is repayable in the event the goods or services are not in fact sold, hired or otherwise provided;`
  line `( ii ) advance received in connection with consideration of an immovable property under an`
  line `agreement or arrangement subject to the condition that such advance is adjusted against such`
  line `immovable property as specified in terms of the agreement or ar rangement;`
  line `( iii ) security or dealership deposited for the performance of the contract for supply of goods or`
  line `provision of services; or`
  line `( iv ) an advance under the long - term projects for supply of capital goods except those specified`
  line `in item ( ii ):`
  line `Provided t hat if the amounts received under items ( i ) to ( iv ) become refundable, such amounts`
  line `shall be deemed to be deposits on the expiry of fifteen days from the date on which they become`
  line `due for refund:`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-5
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Page 5`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  sourcePage 5
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line 5
  line `Provided further that where the said amounts become refunda ble, due to the deposit taker not`
  line `obtaining necessary permission or approval under the law for the time being in force, wherever`
  line `required, to deal in the goods or properties or services for which money is taken, such amounts`
  line `shall be deemed to be deposits.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this clause, —`
  line `( i ) in respect of a company, the expression “deposit” shall have the same meaning as assigned`
  line `to it under the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013);`
  line `( ii ) in respect of a non - banking financial company registered under the Reserve Bank of India`
  line `Act, 1934 (2 of 1934), the expression “deposit” shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in`
  line `clause ( bb ) of section 45 - I of the said Act;`
  line `( iii ) the expressions “partner” and “firm” shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them`
  line `under the Indian Partnership Act, 1932 (9 of 1932);`
  line `( iv ) the expression “partner” in respect of a limited liability partnership shall have the same`
  line `meaning as assigned to it in clause ( q ) of sub - section ( 1 ) of section 2 of the Limited Lia bility`
  line `Partnership Act, 2008 (6 of 2009);`
  line `( v ) the expression “relative” shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in the Companies`
  line `Act, 2013 (18 of 2013);`
  line `( 5 ) “depositor” means any person who makes a deposit under this Act;`
  line `( 6 ) “deposit taker” means —`
  line `( i ) any individual or group of individuals;`
  line `( ii ) a proprietorship concern;`
  line `( iii ) a partnership firm (whether registered or not);`
  line `( iv ) a limited liability partnership registered under the Limited Liability Partnership Act, 2008 (6 of`
  line `2009);`
  line `( v ) a compan y;`
  line `( vi ) an association of persons;`
  line `( vii ) a trust (being a private trust governed under the provisions of the Indian Trusts Act, 1882 (2 of`
  line `1882) or a public trust, whether registered or not);`
  line `( viii ) a co - operative society or a multi - State co - operative society; or`
  line `( ix ) any other arrangement of whatsoever nature, receiving or soliciting deposits, but does not`
  line `include —`
  line `( i ) a Corporation incorporated under an Act of Parliament or a State Legislature;`
  line `( ii ) a banking company, a corresponding new bank, the State Bank of India, a subsidiary bank, a`
  line `regional rural bank, a co - operative bank or a multi - State co - operative bank as defined in the`
  line `Banking Regulation Act,1949 (10 of 1949);`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-6
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Page 6`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  sourcePage 6
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line 6
  line `( 7 ) “Designated Court” mean s a Designated Court constituted by the appropriate Government under`
  line `section 8;`
  line `( 8 ) “insurer” shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in clause ( 9 ) of section 2 of the Insurance`
  line `Act, 1938 (4 of 1938);`
  line `( 9 ) “notification” means a notification publish ed in the Official Gazette and the expression “notify”`
  line `shall be construed accordingly;`
  line `( 10 ) “person” includes —`
  line `( i ) an individual;`
  line `( ii ) a Hindu Undivided Family;`
  line `( iii ) a company;`
  line `( iv ) a trust;`
  line `( v ) a partnership firm;`
  line `( vi ) a limited liability partnership;`
  line `( vii ) an association of persons;`
  line `( viii ) a co - operative society registered under any law for the time being in force relating to`
  line `co - operative societies; or`
  line `( ix ) every artificial juridical person, not falling within any of the preceding sub - clauses;`
  line `( 11 ) “prescribed” means prescribed by the rules made by the Central Government or, as the case may`
  line `be, the State Government under this Act;`
  line `( 12 ) “property” means any propert y or assets of every description, whether corporeal or incorporeal,`
  line `movable or immovable, tangible or intangible, and includes deeds and instruments evidencing title to, or`
  line `interest in, such property or assets, wherever located;`
  line `( 13 ) “public financial inst itution” shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in clause ( 72 ) of`
  line `section 2 of the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013);`
  line `( 14 ) “Regulated Deposit Scheme” means the Schemes specified under column ( 3 ) of the First`
  line Schedule;
  line `( 15 ) “Regulator” means the Reg ulator specified in column ( 2 ) of the First Schedule;`
  line `( 16 ) “Schedule” means the Schedule appended to this Act;`
  line `( 17 ) “Unregulated Deposit Scheme” means a Scheme or an arrangement under which deposits are`
  line `accepted or solicited by any deposit taker by way o f business and which is not a Regulated Deposit`
  line `Scheme, as specified under column ( 3 ) of the First Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-7
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Page 7`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  sourcePage 7
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line 7
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line `Union Territory of Jammu and Kashmir`
  line `Section 2. — In clause (1), in sub - clause (iii), omit "and" and after sub - clause (iii) as so omitted,`
  line `insert —`
  line `“(iiia) the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir, the Government of that Union territory; and”.`
  line `[ Vide Union Territory of Jammu and Kashmir Reorganisation (Adapta tion of Central Laws) Second`
  line `Order, 2020, Notification No. S.O. 3465(E), dated (5 - 10 - 2020). ]`
  line `CHAPTER II`
  line `B ANNING OF U NREGULATED D EPOSIT S CHEMES`
  line `3. Banning of Unregulated Deposit Schemes. — On and from the date of commencement of this`
  line `Act, —`
  line `( a ) the Unregulated Deposit Schemes shall be banned; and`
  line `( b ) no deposit taker shall, directly or indirectly, promote, operate, issue any advertisement soliciting`
  line `participation or enrolment in or accept deposits in pursuance of an Unregulated Deposit Scheme.`
  line `4. F raudulent default in Regulated Deposit Schemes. — No deposit taker, while accepting deposits`
  line `pursuant to a Regulated Deposit Scheme, shall commit any fraudulent default in the repayment or return`
  line `of deposit on maturity or in rendering any specified service promised against such deposit.`
  line `5. Wrongful inducement in relation to Unregulated Deposit Schemes. — No person by whatever`
  line `name called shall knowingly make any statement, promise or forecast which is false, deceptive or`
  line `misleading in material facts or delibe rately conceal any material facts, to induce another person to invest`
  line `in, or become a member or participant of any Unregulated Deposit Scheme.`
  line `6. Certain scheme to be Unregulated Deposit Scheme. — A prize chit or a money circulation scheme`
  line `banned under the p rovisions of the Prize Chits and Money Circulation Scheme (Banning) Act, 1978 (43 of`
  line `1978) shall be deemed to be an Unregulated Deposit Scheme under this Act.`
  line `CHAPTER III`
  line `A UTHORITIES`
  line `7. Competent Authority. — ( 1 ) The appropriate Government shall, by notification, appoint one or`
  line `more officers not below the rank of Secretary to that Government, as the Competent Authority for the`
  line `purposes of this Act.`
  line `( 2 ) The appropriate Government may, by notification, appoint such othe r officer or officers as it thinks`
  line `fit, to assist the Competent Authority in discharging its functions under this Act.`
  line `( 3 ) Where the Competent Authority or officers appointed under sub - section ( 2 ), for the purposes of`
  line `this section, has reason to believe (t he reason for such belief to be recorded in writing), on the basis of`
  line `such information and particulars as may be prescribed, that any deposit taker is soliciting deposits in`
  line `contravention of section 3, he may, by an order in writing, provisionally attach t he deposits held by the`
  line `deposit taker and the money or other property acquired either in the name of the deposit taker or in the`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-8
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Page 8`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  sourcePage 8
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line 8
  line `name of any other person on behalf of the deposit taker from the date of the order, in such manner as may`
  line `be prescribed.`
  line `( 4 ) The Competent Authority shall, for the purposes of sub - section ( 3 ), have the same powers as vested`
  line `in a civil court under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) while conducting investigation or`
  line `inquiry in respect of the following matters, namely: —`
  line `( a ) discovery and inspection;`
  line `( b ) enforcing the attendance of any person, including any officer of a reporting entity and`
  line `examining him on oath;`
  line `( c ) compelling the production of records;`
  line `( d ) receiving evidence on affidavits;`
  line `( e ) issuing commissions for examination of witnesses and documents; and`
  line `( f ) any other matter which may be prescribed.`
  line `( 5 ) The Competent Authority shall have power to summon any person whose attendance he considers`
  line `necessary whether to give evidence or to produce any records during the course of any investigation or`
  line `proceeding under this section.`
  line `( 6 ) All the persons so summoned shall be bound to attend in person or through authorised agents, as`
  line `such officer may direct, and shall be bound to state the truth upon any subject respectin g which they are`
  line `examined or make statements, and produce such documents as may be required.`
  line `( 7 ) Every proceeding under sub - sections ( 4 ) and ( 5 ) shall be deemed to be a judicial proceeding within`
  line `the meaning of section 193 and section 228 of the Indian Pe nal Code (45 of 1860).`
  line `( 8 ) Subject to any rules made in this behalf by the Central Government, any officer referred to in sub -`
  line `section ( 2 ) may impound and retain in his custody for such period, as he thinks fit, any records produced`
  line `before him in any proceedings under this Act:`
  line `Provided that the officer or officers referred to in sub - section ( 2 ) shall not —`
  line `( a ) impound any records without recording his reasons for so doing; or`
  line `( b ) retain in his custody any such records for a period exceeding three mon ths, without obtaining`
  line `the previous approval of the Competent Authority.`
  line `8. Designated Court. — ( 1 ) The appropriate Government shall, with the concurrence of the Chief`
  line `Justice of the concerned High Court, by notification, constitute one or more Courts kno wn as the`
  line `Designated Courts for such area or areas or such case or cases as may be specified in such notification,`
  line `which shall be presided over by a Judge not below the rank of a District and Sessions Judge or Additional`
  line `District and Sessions Judge.`
  line `( 2 ) No Court other than the Designated Court shall have jurisdiction in respect of any matter to which`
  line `the provisions of this Act apply.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-9
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Page 9`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  sourcePage 9
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line 9
  line `( 3 ) When trying an offence under this Act, the Designated Court may also try an offence, other than an`
  line `offence under this Ac t, with which the accused may, under the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of`
  line `1974), be charged at the same trial.`
  line `CHAPTER IV`
  line `I NFORMATION ON DEPOSIT TAKERS`
  line `9. Central database. — ( 1 ) The Central Government may designate an authority, whether existing or`
  line `to be constituted, which shall create, maintain and operate an online database for information on deposit`
  line `takers operating in India.`
  line `( 2 ) The authority designated under sub - section ( 1 ) may require any Regulator or the Competent`
  line `Authority to share such information on deposit takers, as may be prescribed.`
  line `10. Information of business by deposit taker. — ( 1 ) Every deposit taker which commences or carries`
  line `on its business as such on or after the commencement of this Act shall intimate the authority referred to in`
  line `sub - section ( 1 ) of section 9 about its business in such form and manner and within such time, as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line `( 2 ) The Competent Authority may, if it has reason to believe that t he deposits are being solicited or`
  line `accepted pursuant to an Unregulated Deposit Scheme, direct any deposit taker to furnish such statements,`
  line `information or particulars, as it considers necessary, relating to or connected with the deposits received by`
  line `such d eposit taker.`
  line `Explanation. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby clarified that —`
  line `( a ) the requirement of intimation under sub - section ( 1 ) is applicable to deposit takers accepting or`
  line `soliciting deposits as defined in clause ( 4 ) of section 2; and`
  line `( b ) the requirement of intimation under sub - section ( 1 ) applies to a company, if the company`
  line `accepts the deposits under Chapter V of the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013).`
  line `11. Information to be shared. — ( 1 ) The Competent Authority shall share all information rec eived`
  line `under section 29 with the Central Bureau of Investigation and with the authority which may be designated`
  line `by the Central Government under section 9.`
  line `( 2 ) The appropriate Government, any Regulator, income - tax authorities or any other investigation`
  line `agen cy, having any information or documents in respect of the offence investigated under this Act by the`
  line `police or the Central Bureau of Investigation, shall share all such information or documents with the`
  line `police or the Central Bureau of Investigation.`
  line `( 3 ) W here the principal officer of any banking company, a corresponding new bank, the State Bank of`
  line `India, a subsidiary bank, a regional rural bank, a co - operative bank or a multi - State co - operative bank has`
  line `reason to believe that any client is a deposit taker and is acting in contravention to the provisions of this`
  line `Act, he shall forthwith inform the same to the Competent Authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-10
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Page 10`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  sourcePage 10
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line 10
  line `CHAPTER V`
  line `R ESTITUTION TO DEPOSITORS`
  line `12. Priority of depositors ’ claim. — Save as otherwise provided in the Securitisation and`
  line `Rec onstruction of Financial Assets and Enforcement of Security Interest Act, 2002 (54 of 2002) or the`
  line `Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code, 2016 (31 of 2016), any amount due to depositors from a deposit taker`
  line `shall be paid in priority over all other debts and all r evenues, taxes, cesses and other rates payable to the`
  line `appropriate Government or the local authority.`
  line `13. Precedence of attachment. — ( 1 ) Save as otherwise provided in the Securitisation and`
  line `Reconstruction of Financial Assets and Enforcement of Security In terest Act, 2002 ( 54 of 2002 ) or the`
  line `Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code, 2016 (31 of 2016), an order of provisional attachment passed by the`
  line `Competent Authority, shall have precedence and priority, to the extent of the claims of the depositors,`
  line `over any other attachment by any authority competent to attach property for repayment of any debts,`
  line `r evenues, taxes, cesses and other rates payable to the appropriate Government or the local authority.`
  line `( 2 ) Where an order of provisional attachment has been passed by the Competent Authority —`
  line `( a ) such attachment shall continue until an order is passed under sub - section ( 3 ) or sub - section ( 5 )`
  line `of section 15 by the Designated Court;`
  line `( b ) all the attached money or property of the deposit taker and the persons mentioned therein shall`
  line `vest in the Competent Authority and shall remain so vested till further order of the Designated Court.`
  line `( 3 ) The Competent Authority shall open an account in a sche duled bank for the purpose of crediting`
  line `and dealing with the money realised under this Act, which shall not be utilised except under the`
  line `instructions of the Designated Court.`
  line `( 4 ) The Competent Authority shall not dispose of or alienate the property or mon ey attached, except in`
  line `accordance with the order of the Designated Court under sub - section ( 3 ) or sub - section ( 5 ) of section 15.`
  line `( 5 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub - section ( 4 ), the Competent Authority may, if it thinks it`
  line `expedient, order the im mediate sale of perishable items or assets, and the proceeds of the sale shall be`
  line `utilised in the same manner as provided for other property.`
  line `14. Application for confirmation of attachment and sale of property. — ( 1 ) The Competent`
  line `Authority shall, within a p eriod of thirty days, which may extend up to sixty days, for reasons to be`
  line `recorded in writing, from the date of the order of provisional attachment, file an application with such`
  line `particulars as may be prescribed, before the Designated Court for making the provisional attachment`
  line `absolute, and for permission to sell the property so attached by public auction or, if necessary, by private`
  line sale.
  line `( 2 ) In case where the money or property has been attached on the permission granted by a Designated`
  line `Court in another State or Union territory, the application for confirmation of such attachment shall be filed`
  line `in that Court.`
  line `15. Confirmation of attachment by Designated Court. — ( 1 ) Upon receipt of an application under`
  line `section 14, the Designated Court shall issue notice t o —`
  line `( a ) the deposit taker; and`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-11
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Page 11`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  sourcePage 11
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line 11
  line `( b ) any person whose property is attached under section 14,`
  line `to show cause, within a period of thirty days from the date of issue of notice, as to why the order of`
  line `attachment should not be made absolute and the properties so attached be sold.`
  line `( 2 ) The Designated Court shall also issue notice to all other persons represented to it as having or`
  line `being likely to claim any interest or title in the property, to appear on the same date as persons referred to`
  line `in sub - section ( 1 ) to raise objections, if they so desire, to the attachment of the property.`
  line `( 3 ) The Designated Court shall, after adopting such procedure as may be prescribed, pass an order —`
  line `( a ) making the provisional order of attachment absolute; or`
  line `( b ) varying it by releas ing a portion of the property from attachment; or`
  line `( c ) cancelling the provisional order of attachment, and in case of an order under clause ( a ) or clause`
  line `( b ), direct the Competent Authority to sell the property so attached by public auction or, if necessar y,`
  line `by private sale and realise the sale proceeds.`
  line `( 4 ) The Designated Court shall not, in varying or cancelling the provisional order of attachment,`
  line `release any property from attachment, unless it is satisfied that —`
  line `( a ) the deposit taker or the person ref erred to in sub - section ( 1 ) has interest in such property; and`
  line `( b ) there shall remain an amount or property sufficient for repayment to the depositors of such`
  line `deposit taker.`
  line `( 5 ) The Designated Court shall pass such order or issue such direction as may be necessary for the`
  line `equitable distribution among the depositors of the money attached or realised out of the sale.`
  line `( 6 ) The Designated Court shall endeavour to complete the procee dings under this section within a`
  line `period of one hundred and eighty days from the date of receipt of the application referred to in`
  line `sub - section ( 1 ).`
  line `16. Attachment of property of mala fide transferees. — ( 1 ) Where the Designated Court is satisfied`
  line `that there is a reasonable cause for believing that the deposit taker has transferred any property otherwise`
  line `than in good faith and not for commensurate consideration, it may, by notice, require any transferee of`
  line `such property, whether or not he received the property directly from the said deposit taker, to appear on a`
  line `date to be specified in the notice and show cause why so much of the transferee’s property as is equivalent`
  line `to the proper value of the property transferred should not be attached.`
  line `( 2) Where the said transferee does not appear and show cause on the specified date or where the`
  line `Designated Court is satisfied that the transfer of the property to the said transferee was not a bona fide`
  line `transfer and not for commensurate consideration, it sh all order the attachment of so much of the said`
  line `transferee’s property as in its opinion is equivalent to the proper value of the property transferred.`
  line `17. Payment in lieu of attachment. — ( 1 ) Any deposit taker or a person referred to in su b -`
  line `section ( 1 ) of section 15, or transferee referred to in section 16 whose property is about to be attached or`
  line `has been provisionally attached under this Act, may, at any time before the confirmation of attachment,`
  line `apply to the Designated Court for permiss ion to deposit the fair value of the property in lieu of`
  line attachment.
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-12
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Page 12`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  sourcePage 12
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line 12
  line `( 2 ) While allowing the deposit taker or person or transferee referred to in sub - section ( 1 ) to make the`
  line `deposit under sub - section ( 1 ), the Designated Court may order such deposit taker o r person or transferee`
  line `to pay any sum towards costs as may be applicable.`
  line `18. Powers of Designated Court. — ( 1 ) The Designated Court shall exercise the following powers,`
  line `namely: —`
  line `( a ) power to approve the statement of dues of the deposit taker due from var ious debtors;`
  line `( b ) power to assess the value of the assets of the deposit taker and finalise the list of the depositors`
  line `and their respective dues;`
  line `( c ) power to direct the Competent Authority to take possession of any assets belonging to or in the`
  line `control o f the deposit taker and to sell, transfer or realise the attached assets, either by public auction or`
  line `by private sale as it deems fit depending upon the nature of assets and credit the sale proceeds thereof`
  line `to its bank account;`
  line `( d ) power to approve the nec essary expenditure to be incurred by the Competent Authority for`
  line `taking possession and realisation of the assets of the deposit taker;`
  line `( e ) power to pass an order for full payment to the depositors by the Competent Authority or an`
  line `order for proportionate pa yment to the depositors in the event, the money so realised is not sufficient to`
  line `meet the entire deposit liability;`
  line `( f ) power to direct any person, who has made profit or averted loss by indulging in any transaction`
  line `or activity in contravention of the prov isions of this Act, to disgorge an amount equivalent to the`
  line `wrongful gain made or loss averted by such contravention; and`
  line `( g ) power to pass any other order which the Designated Court deems fit for realisation of assets of`
  line `the deposit taker and for repayment of the same to the depositors of such deposit taker or on any other`
  line `matter or issue incidental thereto.`
  line `( 2 ) On the application of any person interested in any property attached and vested in the Competent`
  line `Authority under this Act and after giving such Competent Authority an opportunity of being heard, make`
  line `such order as the Designated Court considers just and reasonable for —`
  line `( a ) providing from such of the property attached and vested in the Competent Autho rity as the`
  line `applicant claims an interest in, such sums as may be reasonably necessary for the maintenance of the`
  line `applicant and of his family, and for expenses connected with the defence of the applicant where`
  line `criminal proceedings have been initiated agains t him in the Designated Court under this Act; or`
  line `( b ) safeguarding, so far as may be practicable, the interest of any business affected by the`
  line attachment.
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, the expression “deposit taker” includes the`
  line `directors, promoters, managers or members of said establishment or any other person whose property`
  line `or assets have been attached under this Act.`
  line `19. Appeal to High Court. — Any person including the Competent Authority, if aggrieved by any`
  line `final order of the Designate d Court under this Chapter, may appeal to the High Court, within a period of`
  line `sixty days from the date of such order:`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-13
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Page 13`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  sourcePage 13
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line 13
  line `Provided that the High Court may entertain the appeal after the expiry of the said period of sixty days,`
  line `if it is satisfied that the appell ant was prevented by sufficient cause from preferring the appeal in time.`
  line `Explanation. — The expression “High Court” means the High Court of a State or Union territory where`
  line `the Designated Court is situated.`
  line `20. Power of Supreme Court to transfer cases. — ( 1 ) Whenever it is made to appear to the Supreme`
  line `Court that there is a default in any deposit scheme or deposit schemes of the nature referred to in section`
  line `30, the Supreme Court may, by an order, direct that any particular case be transferred from one`
  line `Desi gnated Court to another Designated Court.`
  line `( 2 ) The Supreme Court may act under this section only on an application filed by the Competent`
  line `Authority or any interested party, and every such application shall be supported by an affidavit.`
  line `( 3 ) Where an application for the exercise of the powers conferred by this section is dismissed, the`
  line `Supreme Court may, if it is of opinion that the application was frivolous or vexatious, order the applicant`
  line `to pay by way of compensation to any person who has opposed t he application such sum not exceeding`
  line `fifty thousand rupees as it may consider appropriate in the circumstances of the case.`
  line `CHAPTER VI`
  line `O FFENCES AND PUNISHMENTS`
  line `21. Punishment for contravention of section 3. — ( 1 ) Any deposit taker who solicits deposits in`
  line `contravention of section 3 shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than`
  line `one year but which may extend to five years and with fine which shall not be less than two lakh rupees but`
  line `which may extend to ten lakh rupees.`
  line `( 2 ) An y deposit taker who accepts deposits in contravention of section 3 shall be punishable with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than two years but which may extend to seven years and`
  line `with fine which shall not be less than three lakh rupees but which may extend to ten lakh rupees.`
  line `( 3 ) Any deposit taker who accepts deposits in contravention of section 3 and fraudulently defaults in`
  line `repayment of such deposits or in rendering any specified service, shall be punishable with imprisonment`
  line `for a term wh ich shall not be less than three years but which may extend to ten years and with fine which`
  line `shall not be less than five lakh rupees but which may extend to twice the amount of aggregate funds`
  line `collected from the subscribers, members or participants in the Unregulated Deposit Scheme.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this Act, —`
  line `( i ) the expression “fraudulently” shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in section 25 of the`
  line `Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860);`
  line `( ii ) where the terms of the Deposit Scheme are enti rely impracticable or unviable, the terms shall be`
  line `relevant facts showing an intention to defraud.`
  line `22. Punishment for contravention of section 4. — Any deposit taker who contravenes the provisions`
  line `of section 4 shall be punishable with imprisonment for a te rm which may extend to seven years, or with`
  line `fine which shall not be less than five lakh rupees but which may extend to twenty - five crore rupees or`
  line `three times the amount of profits made out of the fraudulent default referred to in said section, whichever`
  line `i s higher, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-14
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Page 14`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  sourcePage 14
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line 14
  line `23. Punishment for contravention of section 5. — Any person who contravenes the provisions of`
  line `section 5 shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than one year but`
  line `which may extend to five years and with fine which may extend to ten lakh rupees.`
  line `24. Punishment for repeat o ffenders. — Whoever having been previously convicted of an offence`
  line `punishable under this Chapter, except the offence under section 26, is subsequently convicted of an`
  line `offence shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than five years but which`
  line `may extend to ten years and with fine which shall not be less than ten lakh rupees but which may extend`
  line `to fifty crore rupees.`
  line `25. Offences by deposit takers other than individuals. — ( 1 ) Where an offence under this Act has`
  line `been committed by a deposit taker other than an individual, every person who, at the time the offence was`
  line `committed, was in charge of, and was responsible to, the deposit taker for the conduct of its business, as`
  line `well as the deposit taker, shall be deemed to be guilty o f the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded`
  line `against and punished accordingly.`
  line `( 2 ) Nothing contained in sub - section ( 1 ) shall render any such person liable to any punishment`
  line `provided in this Act, if he proves that the offence was committed without hi s knowledge or that he`
  line `exercised all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line `( 3 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub - section ( 1 ), where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a deposit taker other than an individual, and it is proved that the offence —`
  line `( a ) has been committed with the consent or connivance of; or`
  line `( b ) is attributable to any neglect on the part of any director, manager, secretary, promoter, partner,`
  line `employee or other officer of the deposit taker,`
  line `such person s hall also be deemed to be guilty of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against`
  line `and punished accordingly.`
  line `26. Punishment for contravention of section 10. — Whoever fails to give the intimation required`
  line `under sub - section ( 1 ) of section 10 or fails to furnish any such statements, information or particulars as`
  line `required under sub - section ( 2 ) of that section, shall be punishable with fine which may extend to five lakh`
  line rupees.
  line `27. Cognizance of offences. — Notwithstanding anything contained in section 4, no Designated Court`
  line `shall take cognizance of an offence punishable under that section except upon a complaint made by the`
  line `Regulator:`
  line `Provided that the provisions of section 4 and this section shall not appl y in relation to a deposit taker`
  line `which is a company.`
  line `CHAPTER VII`
  line `I NVESTIGATION, SEARCH AND SEIZURE`
  line `28. Offences to be cognizable and non - bailable. — Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code`
  line `of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) every offence punisha ble under this Act, except the offence`
  line `under section 22 and section 26, shall be cognizable and non - bailable.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-15
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Page 15`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  sourcePage 15
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line 15
  line `29. Competent Authority to be informed of offences. — The police officer shall, on recording`
  line `information about the commission of an offence under t his Act, inform the same to the Competent`
  line Authority.
  line `30. Investigation of offences by Central Bureau of Investigation. — ( 1 ) On receipt of information`
  line `under section 29 or otherwise, if the Competent Authority has reason to believe that the offence relates to`
  line `a deposit scheme or deposit schemes in which —`
  line `( a ) the depositors, deposit takers or properties involved are located in more than one State or Union`
  line `territory in India or outside India; and`
  line `( b ) the total value of the amount involved is of such magnitude as to significantly affect the public`
  line interest,
  line `the Competent Authority shall refer the matter to the Central Government for investigation by the Central`
  line `Bureau of Investigation.`
  line `( 2 ) The reference ma de by the Competent Authority under sub - section ( 1 ) shall be deemed to be with`
  line `the consent of the State Government under section 6 of the Delhi Special Police Establishment Act, 1946`
  line `(25 of 1946).`
  line `( 3 ) On the receipt of the reference under sub - section ( 1 ), the Central Government may transfer the`
  line `investigation of the offence to the Central Bureau of Investigation under section 5 of the Delhi Special`
  line `Police Establishment Act, 1946 (25 of 1946).`
  line `31. Power to enter, search and seize without warrant. — ( 1 ) Whenev er any police officer, not`
  line `below the rank of an officer in - charge of a police station, has reason to believe that anything necessary for`
  line `the purpose of an investigation into any offence under this Act may be found in any place within the limits`
  line `of the poli ce station of which he is in - charge, or to which he is attached, such officer may, with the written`
  line `authorisation of an officer not below the rank of Superintendent of Police, and after recording in writing`
  line `so far as possible, the thing for which the searc h is to be made and subject to the rules made in this behalf,`
  line `authorise any officer subordinate to him, —`
  line `( a ) to enter and search any building, conveyance or place, between sunrise and sunset, which he has`
  line `reason to suspect is being used for purposes connec ted with the promotion or conduct of any deposit`
  line `taking scheme or arrangement in contravention of the provisions of this Act;`
  line `( b ) in case of resistance, to break open any door and remove any obstacle to such entry, if necessary`
  line `by force, with such assistan ce as he considers necessary, for exercising the powers conferred by clause`
  line `( a );`
  line `( c ) to seize any record or property found as a result of the search in the said building, conveyance or`
  line `place, which are intended to be used, or reasonably suspected to have been used, in connection with`
  line `any such deposit taking scheme or arrangement in contravention of the provisions of this Act; and`
  line `( d ) to detain and search, and if he thinks proper, take into custody and produce before any`
  line `Designated Court any such person wh om he has reason to believe to have committed any offence`
  line `punishable under this Act:`
  line `Provided that if such officer has reason to believe that the said written authorisation cannot be`
  line `obtained without affording opportunity for the concealment of evidence o r facility for the escape of an`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-16
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Page 16`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  sourcePage 16
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line 16
  line `offender, he may, without the said written authorisation, enter and search such building, conveyance or`
  line `place, at any time between sunset and sunrise after recording the grounds in writing.`
  line `( 2 ) Where it is not practicable to seize the record or property, the officer authorised under sub - section`
  line `( 1 ), may make an order in writing to freeze such property, account, deposits or valuable securities`
  line `maintained by any deposit taker about which a compla int has been made or credible information has been`
  line `received or a reasonable suspicion exists of their having been connected with the promotion or conduct of`
  line `any deposit taking scheme or arrangement in contravention of the provisions of this Act and it shal l be`
  line `binding on the concerned bank or financial or market establishment to comply with the said order:`
  line `Provided that no bank or financial or market establishment shall freeze such account, deposit or`
  line `valuable securities, for a period beyond thirty days unl ess the same is authorised by the order of the`
  line `Designated Court:`
  line `Provided further that, if at any time, it becomes practicable to seize the frozen property, the officer`
  line `authorised under sub - section ( 1 ) may seize such property.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purpose s of this section, the expressions, —`
  line `( i ) “freezing of account” shall mean that no transaction, whether deposit or withdrawal shall be`
  line `allowed in the said account; and`
  line `( ii ) “freezing of property” shall mean that no transfer, conversion, disposition or move ment of`
  line `property shall be allowed.`
  line `( 3 ) Where an officer takes down any information in writing or records grounds for his belief or makes`
  line `an order in writing under sub - section ( 1 ) or sub - section ( 2 ), he shall, within a time of seventy - two hours`
  line `send a copy thereof to the Designated Court in a sealed envelope and the owner or occupier of the`
  line `building, conveyance or place shall, on application, be furnished, free of cost, with a copy of the same by`
  line `the Designated Court.`
  line `( 4 ) All searches, seizures and arrests under this section shall be made in accordance with the provisions`
  line `of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
  line `32. Application of Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 to proceedings before Designated Court. —`
  line `( 1 ) The Designated Court may take cognizance of offences under this Act without the accused being`
  line `committed to it for trial.`
  line `( 2 ) Save as otherwise provided in section 31, the provisions of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973`
  line `(2 of 1974) shall apply —`
  line `( a ) to all arrests, searches and seizu res made under this Act;`
  line `( b ) to the proceedings under this Act and for the purposes of the said provisions, the Designated`
  line `Court shall be deemed to be a Court of Session and the persons conducting the prosecution before the`
  line `Designated Court, shall be deeme d to be Public Prosecutors.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-17
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Page 17`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  sourcePage 17
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line 17
  line `CHAPTER VIII`
  line `M ISCELLANEOUS`
  line `33. Publication of advertisement of Unregulated Deposit Scheme. — Where any newspaper or`
  line `other publication of any nature, contains any statement, information or advertisement promoting,`
  line `soliciting de posits for, or inducing any person to become a member of any Unregulated Deposit Scheme,`
  line `the appropriate Government may direct such newspaper or publication to publish a full and fair retraction,`
  line `free of cost, in the same manner and in the same position in such newspaper or publication as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line `34. Act to have overriding effect. — Save as otherwise expressly provided in this Act, the provisions`
  line `of this Act shall have effect notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being i n`
  line `force, including any law made by any State or Union territory.`
  line `35. Application of other laws not barred. — The provisions of this Act shall be in addition to, and`
  line `not in derogation of, the provisions of any other law for the time being in force.`
  line `36. Prot ection of action taken in good faith. — No suit, prosecution or other legal proceedings shall`
  line `lie against the appropriate Government or the Competent Authority or any officer of the appropriate`
  line `Government for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done under this Act or the rules`
  line `made thereunder.`
  line `37. Power of Central Government to make rules. — ( 1 ) The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification, make rules for carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line `( 2 ) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may provide`
  line `for all or any of the following matters, namely: —`
  line `( a ) the information and other particulars to be taken into consideration before issuing an order, and`
  line `the manner of attachment, under sub - sectio n ( 3 ) of section 7;`
  line `( b ) the information to be shared under sub - section ( 2 ) of section 9;`
  line `( c ) the form and manner in which and the time within which the intimation shall be given under`
  line `sub - section ( 1 ) of section 10;`
  line `( d ) the particulars contained in the application to be filed by the Competent Authority before the`
  line `Designated Court under sub - section ( 1 ) of section 14;`
  line `( e ) the procedure to be adopted by the Designated Court before issuing an order under sub - section`
  line `( 3 ) of sec tion 15;`
  line `( f ) rules under sub - section ( 1 ) of section 31;`
  line `( g ) the manner of publication of advertisement under section 33; and`
  line `( h ) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line `38. Power of State Government, etc., to make rules. — ( 1 ) Th e State Government or Union territory`
  line `Government, as the case may be, in consultation with the Central Government, by notification, make rules`
  line `for carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-18
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Page 18`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  sourcePage 18
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line 18
  line `( 2 ) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may provide`
  line `for all or any of the following matters, namely: —`
  line `( a ) ceiling for self - help groups under clause (j) of sub - section (4) of section 2;`
  line `( b ) purpose and ceiling under clause (k) of sub - section (4) of section 2;`
  line `( c ) the manner of provisional attachment of property by the Competent Authority under sub - section`
  line `( 3 ) of section 7;`
  line `( d ) other matters under clause ( f ) of sub - section ( 4 ) of section 7;`
  line `( e ) the rules relating to impounding and custody of records under sub - section ( 8 ) of section 7; and`
  line `( f ) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line `39. Laying of rules. — ( 1 ) Every rule made by the Central Government under this Act shall be laid, as`
  line `soon as may be after it is made, before each House of Parliame nt, while it is in session, for a total period`
  line `of thirty days which may be comprised in one session, or in two or more successive sessions, and if,`
  line `before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid,`
  line `bot h Houses agree in making any modification in the rule, or both Houses agree that the rule should not`
  line `be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case`
  line `may be; so, however, that any such modification o r annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of`
  line `anything previously done under that rule.`
  line `( 2 ) Every rule made by a State Government or the Union territory Government, as the case may be,`
  line `shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before e ach House of the State Legislature or the Union`
  line `territory Legislature, as the case may be, where it consists of two Houses, or where such Legislature`
  line `consists of one House, before that House.`
  line `40. Power to amend First Schedule. — ( 1 ) The Central Government may, having regard to the`
  line `objects of this Act, and if it considers necessary or expedient so to do, by notification, add to, or as the`
  line `case may be, omit from the First Schedule, any scheme or arrangement, and on such addition, or`
  line `omission, such scheme or a rrangement shall become, or cease to be, a Regulated Deposit Scheme, as the`
  line `case may be.`
  line `( 2 ) A copy of every notification issued under this section shall, as soon as may be after it has been`
  line `issued, be laid before each House of Parliament.`
  line `41. Act not to a pply certain deposits. — The provisions of this Act shall not apply to deposits taken`
  line `in the ordinary course of business.`
  line `42. Amendment to certain enactments. — The enactments specified in the Second Schedule shall be`
  line `amended in the manner specified therein.`
  line `43. Power to remove difficulties. — ( 1 ) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions,`
  line `not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, as may appear to it to be necessary for removing the`
  line `difficulty:`
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made under this section after the expiry of three years from the`
  line `commencement of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
